# ============================================================================
# DOCKERIGNORE - Files/Directories Excluded from Docker Build
# ============================================================================
#
# WHAT IS THIS?
# - List of files/directories Docker should NOT copy to image
# - Keeps Docker images smaller and builds faster
# - Similar to .gitignore but for Docker
#
# WHY EXCLUDE THEM?
# - node_modules: Will be reinstalled in container via npm install
# - Source code (.ts, jest.config, tsconfig, .eslintrc): Not needed in production
# - Git files: Version control not needed in production container
# - Environment files (.env): Secrets should never be in Docker image
# - Logs: Temporary files that build up, waste space
#
# ============================================================================

# Dependencies (reinstalled via npm ci)
node_modules
npm-debug.log

# Build artifacts (rebuilt from source in Dockerfile)
dist

# Source files (not needed in production Docker image)
src

# Configuration files (only needed for development/build)
tsconfig.json
jest.config.json
.eslintrc.json

# Version control (not needed in running container)
.git
.gitignore

# Environment secrets (NEVER put in Docker image)
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local

# Development files (not needed in production)
README.md
BOILERPLATE.md

# Logs (clean slate for each container)
*.log
logs/

